Part of a six-storey residential
building in  China â€™s northern Hebei province collapsed after an
explosion today, injuring at least 27 people, the official
Xinhua News Agency reported, citing local authorities.  Three were in a critical condition, Xinhua said, citing an
unidentified spokesman with the local government in Baoding.
Rescue work is still under way and the cause of the accident is
being investigated, the report said.  The blast occurred at around 3 p.m. local time, shattering
window glass of buildings 200 meters away, Xinhua reported.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
